  "texts": [
    "GPT-3.5 (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) is a third-generation, autoregressive language model that uses deep learning to produce human-like text.",
    "More generally, it can be defined as a computational system designed to generate sequences of words, code, or other data, starting from a source input called 'the prompt' (Floridi & Chiriatti, 2020).",
    "This type of statistical model needs to be trained with large internet datasets made up of texts to produce relevant results.",
    "ChatGPT is the chatbot that uses GPT-3.5 and was released freely to the public in November 2022, reaching the record figure of 1 million users in only one week (Moe, 2022).",
    "Given its flexibility, for many people it is already part of their daily routine of work, study, and research to solve multiple tasks."
  ],
